{title: Multiple Verses}

{start_of_verse: Verse 1}
[G]Woke up this [C]morning with the [D]sun
[G]Grabbed my hat and [C]started to [D]run
[Em]Down the hill and [C]through the [D]trees
[G]Dancing with the [C]autumn [D]breeze
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 2}
[G]Found a river [C]clear and [D]wide
[G]Sat down on the [C]river[D]side
[Em]Watched the water [C]rushing [D]past
[G]Moments like these [C]never [D]last
{end_of_verse}

{start_of_verse: Verse 3}
[G]Headed home as [C]stars came [D]out
[G]Fireflies were [C]all a[D]bout
[Em]Crickets singing [C]their sweet [D]song
[G]Night is where I [C]be[D]long
{end_of_verse}
